Diagnostic Summary

Source: R/data.R
DXSUM.Rd

Diagnostic Summary data. More information is available at https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Usage

data(DXSUM)

Format

A data frame with 14686 observations and 42 variables.

Source

https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Details

  • ORIGPROT character Original study protocol , with options: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNI4

  • COLPROT factor Study protocol of data collection , with factor levels: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNI4

  • PTID character Participant ID

  • RID numeric Participant roster ID Range value: 2, ..., 10501

  • VISCODE character Visit code

  • VISCODE2 character Translated visit code

  • EXAMDATE Date Date Form Completed Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • DIAGNOSIS character 1. Which best describes the participant's current diagnosis?

    • ADNI3: 1=CN;2=MCI;3=Dementia

    • ADNI4: 1=CN; 2=MCI; 3=Dementia

    • ADNI1: 1=CN;2=MCI;3=Dementia

    • ADNI2: 1=CN;2=MCI;3=Dementia

    • ADNIGO: 1=CN;2=MCI;3=Dementia

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXNORM character Normal 1=Yes Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXNODEP character Mild Depression 1=Yes Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXMCI character Mild Cognitive Impairment 1=Yes Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXMDES character 2a. MCI features (select all that apply):

    • ADNI1: 1=MCI (Memory features); 2=MCI (Non-memory features)

    • ADNIGO: 1=MCI - Memory features (amnestic); 2=MCI - Non-memory features (non-amnestic)

    • ADNI2: 1=MCI - Memory features (amnestic); 2=MCI - Non-memory features (non-amnestic)

    • ADNI3: 1=MCI - Memory features (amnestic);2=MCI - Non-memory features (non-amnestic)

    • ADNI4: 1=MCI - Memory features (amnestic); 2=MCI - Non-memory features (non-amnestic)

  • DXMPTR1 character i. Subjective memory complaint

    • ADNI1: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNIGO: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNI2: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNI3: 0=No;1=Yes

    • ADNI4: 0=No; 1=Yes

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXMPTR2 character ii. Informant memory complaint

    • ADNI1: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNIGO: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNI2: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNI3: 0=No;1=Yes

    • ADNI4: 0=No; 1=Yes

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXMPTR3 character iii. Normal general cognitive function

    • ADNI1: 1=Yes; 0=No; 2=Marginal

    • ADNIGO: 1=Yes; 0=No; 2=Marginal

    • ADNI2: 1=Yes; 0=No; 2=Marginal

    • ADNI3: 0=No;1=Yes;2=Marginal

    • ADNI4: 0=No; 1=Yes; 2=Marginal

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXMPTR4 character iv. Normal activities of daily living

    • ADNI1: 1=Yes; 0=No; 2=Marginal

    • ADNIGO: 1=Yes; 0=No; 2=Marginal

    • ADNI2: 1=Yes; 0=No; 2=Marginal

    • ADNI3: 0=No;1=Yes;2=Marginal

    • ADNI4: 0=No; 1=Yes; 2=Marginal

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXMPTR5 character v. Objective memory impairment for age and education

    • ADNI1: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNIGO: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNI2: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNI3: 0=No;1=Yes

    • ADNI4: 0=No; 1=Yes

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXMPTR6 character vi. Not demented by diagnostic criteria

    • ADNI1: 1=Yes;0=No

    • ADNIGO: 1=Yes;0=No

    • ADNI2: 1=Yes;0=No

    • ADNI3: 0=No;1=Yes

    • ADNI4: 0=No; 1=Yes

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXMDUE character 2b. Suspected cause of MCI:

    • ADNI1: 1=MCI due to Alzheimer's Disease; 2=MCI due to other etiology

    • ADNIGO: 1=MCI due to Alzheimer's Disease; 2=MCI due to other etiology

    • ADNI2: 1=MCI due to Alzheimer's Disease; 2=MCI due to other etiology

    • ADNI3: 1=MCI due to Alzheimer's Disease;2=MCI due to other etiology

    • ADNI4: 1=MCI due to Alzheimer's Disease; 2=MCI due to other etiology

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXMOTHET character If MCI due to other etiology, select box(es) to indicate reason:

    • ADNI1: 1=Fronto-temporal Dementia; 2=Parkinson's Disease; 3=Huntington's Disease; 4=Progressive Supranuclear Palsy; 8=Corticobasal Degeneration; 9=Vascular Dementia; 10=Prion-Associated Dementia; 14=Other (specify)

    • ADNIGO: 1=Fronto-temporal Dementia; 2=Parkinson's Disease; 3=Huntington's Disease; 4=Progressive Supranuclear Palsy; 5=Alcohol-related Dementia; 6=NPH; 7=Major Depression; 8=Corticobasal Degeneration; 9=Vascular Dementia; 10=Prion-Associated Dementia; 11=HIV; 12=Primary Progressive Aphasia; 13=Posterior Cortical Dysfunction; 14=Other (specify)

    • ADNI2: 1=Fronto-temporal Dementia; 2=Parkinson's Disease; 3=Huntington's Disease; 4=Progressive Supranuclear Palsy; 5=Alcohol-related Dementia; 6=NPH; 7=Major Depression; 8=Corticobasal Degeneration; 9=Vascular Dementia; 10=Prion-Associated Dementia; 11=HIV; 12=Primary Progressive Aphasia; 13=Posterior Cortical Dysfunction; 14=Other (specify)

    • ADNI3: 1=Fronto-temporal Dementia;2=Parkinson's Disease;3=Huntington's Disease;4=Progressive Supranuclear Palsy;5=Alcohol-related Dementia;6=NPH;7=Major Depression;8=Corticobasal Degeneration;9=Vascular Dementia;10=Prion-Associated Dementia;11=HIV;12=Primary Progressive Aphasia;13=Posterior Cortical Dysfunction;14=Other (specify)

    • ADNI4: 1=Fronto-temporal Dementia; 10=Prion-Associated Dementia; 11=HIV; 12=Primary Progressive Aphasia; 13=Posterior Cortical Dysfunction; 14=Other (specify); 2=Parkinson's Disease; 3=Huntington's Disease; 4=Progressive Supranuclear Palsy; 5=Alcohol-related Dementia; 6=NPH; 7=Major Depression; 8=Corticobasal Degeneration; 9=Vascular Dementia

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXDSEV character 3a. Dementia Severity - Clinician's Impression

    • ADNIGO: 1=Mild; 2=Moderate; 3=Severe

    • ADNI2: 1=Mild; 2=Moderate; 3=Severe

    • ADNI3: 1=Mild;2=Moderate;3=Severe

    • ADNI4: 1=Mild; 2=Moderate; 3=Severe

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXDDUE character 3b. Suspected cause of dementia

    • ADNIGO: 1=Dementia due to Alzheimer's Disease; 2=Dementia due to other etiology

    • ADNI2: 1=Dementia due to Alzheimer's Disease; 2=Dementia due to other etiology

    • ADNI3: 1=Dementia due to Alzheimer's Disease;2=Dementia due to other etiology

    • ADNI4: 1=Dementia due to Alzheimer's Disease; 2=Dementia due to other etiology

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXAD character Alzheimer's Disease 1=Yes Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXAPP character If Dementia due to Alzheimer's Disease, indicate likelihood:

    • ADNI1: 1=Probable; 2=Possible

    • ADNIGO: 1=Probable; 2=Possible

    • ADNI2: 1=Probable; 2=Possible

    • ADNI3: 1=Probable;2=Possible

    • ADNI4: 1=Probable; 2=Possible

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXAPROB character If Probable AD, select box(es) for other symptoms present: 1=None;2=Stroke(s);3=Depression;4=Delirium;5=Parkinsonism;6=Metabolic/Toxic Disorder (specify);7=Other (specify) Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXAPOSS character If Possible AD, select box(es) to indicate reason:

    • ADNI1: 1=Atypical clinical course or features (specify); 2=Stroke(s); 3=Depression; 4=Delirium; 5=Parkinsonism; 6=Metabolic / Toxic Disorder (specify); 7=Other (specify)

    • ADNIGO: 1=Atypical clinical course or features (specify); 2=Stroke(s); 3=Depression; 4=Delirium; 5=Parkinsonism; 6=Metabolic / Toxic Disorder (specify); 7=Other (specify)

    • ADNI2: 1=Atypical clinical course or features (specify); 2=Stroke(s); 3=Depression; 4=Delirium; 5=Parkinsonism; 6=Metabolic / Toxic Disorder (specify); 7=Other (specify)

    • ADNI3: 1=Atypical clinical course or features (specify);2=Stroke(s);3=Depression;4=Delirium;5=Parkinsonism;6=Metabolic / Toxic Disorder (specify);7=Other (specify)

    • ADNI4: 1=Atypical clinical course or features (specify); 2=Stroke(s); 3=Depression; 4=Delirium; 5=Parkinsonism; 6=Metabolic / Toxic Disorder (specify); 7=Other (specify)

  • DXPARK character 4b. Parkinsonism symptoms present?

    • ADNI1: 1=Yes

    • ADNIGO: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNI2: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNI3: 0=No;1=Yes

    • ADNI4: 0=No; 1=Yes

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXPDES character If Parkinsonism, select box which indicates best diagnosis: 1=Parkinsonism without cognitive impairment; 2=Parkinsonism with cognitive impairment, not demented; 3=Parkinsonism with cognitive impairment, demented; 4=Atypical Parkinsonism Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXPCOG character If Parkinsonism with cognitive impairment, demented 1=PD;2=PDD;3=DLB;4=PDAD Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXPATYP character If Atypical Parkinsonism 1=PSP;2=CBGD;3=OPCA;4=SND;5=Shy Drager;6=Vascular;7=Other (specify) Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXDEP character 4a. Depressive symptoms present?

    • ADNIGO: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNI2: 1=Yes; 0=No

    • ADNI3: 0=No;1=Yes

    • ADNI4: 0=No; 1=Yes

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXOTHDEM character Other Dementia (not Alzheimer's Disease) 1=Yes Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXODES character If dementia due to other etiology, select best diagnosis:

    • ADNI1: 1=Frontal; 3=Huntington's Disease; 5=Alcohol-related Dementia; 6=NPH; 7=Major Depression; 9=Vascular Dementia; 10=Prion-Associated Dementia; 11=HIV; 12=Primary Progressive Aphasia; 13=Posterior Cortical Dysfunction; 14=Other (specify)

    • ADNIGO: 1=Fronto-temporal Dementia; 2=Parkinson's Disease; 3=Huntington's Disease; 4=Progressive Supranuclear Palsy; 5=Alcohol-related Dementia; 6=NPH; 7=Major Depression; 8=Corticobasal Degeneration; 9=Vascular Dementia; 10=Prion-Associated Dementia; 11=HIV; 12=Primary Progressive Aphasia; 13=Posterior Cortical Dysfunction; 14=Other (specify)

    • ADNI2: 1=Fronto-temporal Dementia; 2=Parkinson's Disease; 3=Huntington's Disease; 4=Progressive Supranuclear Palsy; 5=Alcohol-related Dementia; 6=NPH; 7=Major Depression; 8=Corticobasal Degeneration; 9=Vascular Dementia; 10=Prion-Associated Dementia; 11=HIV; 12=Primary Progressive Aphasia; 13=Posterior Cortical Dysfunction; 14=Other (specify)

    • ADNI3: 1=Fronto-temporal Dementia;2=Parkinson's Disease;3=Huntington's Disease;4=Progressive Supranuclear Palsy;5=Alcohol-related Dementia;6=NPH;7=Major Depression;8=Corticobasal Degeneration;9=Vascular Dementia;10=Prion-Associated Dementia;11=HIV;12=Primary Progressive Aphasia;13=Posterior Cortical Dysfunction;14=Other (specify)

    • ADNI4: 1=Fronto-temporal Dementia; 10=Prion-Associated Dementia; 11=HIV; 12=Primary Progressive Aphasia; 13=Posterior Cortical Dysfunction; 14=Other (specify); 2=Parkinson's Disease; 3=Huntington's Disease; 4=Progressive Supranuclear Palsy; 5=Alcohol-related Dementia; 6=NPH; 7=Major Depression; 8=Corticobasal Degeneration; 9=Vascular Dementia

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • DXCONFID character Physician Confidence in Diagnosis: 1=Uncertain; 2=Mildly Confident; 3=Moderately Confident; 4=Highly Confident Decoded Value: Yes

  • ID numeric Record ID Range value: 2, ..., 185684

  • SITEID numeric Site ID Range value: 1, ..., 941

  • USERDATE Date User Create Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • USERDATE2 Date User Last Modify Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • DD_CRF_VERSION_LABEL character CRF Version Label , with options: v1

  • LANGUAGE_CODE character Language Code e=English Decoded Value: Yes

  • HAS_QC_ERROR character Has Quality Check Error 0=Does not have QC error or QC error has been approved; 1=Has QC error Decoded Value: Yes

  • update_stamp POSIXct POSIXct: YYY-MM-DD
